Document :- it's  thigs you are secrhing for. same as row in database terminology.
Index :- it's collection of document. same as table in databasse terminology. you can have one type of ducment inside one index.

cluster as database.

Documents are hased to a particular shard. each shard may be on a different node in a cluster.

the index has two primary shard and two replica shared.

write request are routed to the primary shard then replicated.
read requests are routed to the primary or any replica.

what is mapping?

A mapping is a schema definition. elasticsearch has resonable defaults but sometimes you need to customize them.

field types,
field index : do you want this field indexed for full text search? 
field analyzer :- tokenizer
